Package: scRDSreport
Type: Package
Title: Reproducible Reports from Single-Cell RDS Files
Version: 0.3.2
Authors@R: person("Anbuengsi", role = c("aut", "cre"), email = "an.bunengsi@qq.com")
Description: Builds reproducible, self-contained single-cell RNA sequencing
    reports from RDS files. Existing Seurat analyses and annotations are
    preserved, minimally processed objects can be completed with the SCP
    package, and a common-species registry connects human, mouse, rat,
    zebrafish, pig, cattle, chicken, dog, and macaque data to matched gene
    identifiers, quality-control patterns, functional resources, and guarded
    optional references. Eligible quality-control, dimensionality, composition,
    differential-expression, enrichment, trajectory, communication,
    cell-cycle, transcription-factor-expression, and copy-number modules are
    run through a fault-isolated analysis plan. Reports include downloadable
    matrices, metadata, result tables, figures, data dictionaries, module
    status, and provenance. Conservative sample-name parsing proposes groups
    and replicates with confidence flags instead of inventing study design.
